# termtris

Terminal Tetris you can install and run as a CLI, with persistent highscores.

## Install (editable or local)
```bash
pip install .
# or
python -m termtris
# or, without installing:
python -m termtris play
```

## Run
```bash
termtris         # start the game
termtris scores  # show top scores
termtris reset   # reset highscores
```

## Controls
- Left/Right: Move
- Down: Soft drop
- Z / X: Rotate left / right
- Space: Hard drop
- P: Pause
- N: New game
- Q: Quit

Scores are stored under your user's config dir (e.g., `~/.config/termtris/termtris.db`).
